parseSQL

public static Schema parseSQL(String schemaString)
                       throws IOException
Parse the given sql-like schema representation into a schema object. Input is expected to be a comma separated list of names and types, where the type is a primitive type, array, map, record, or union. The input will be parsed in a case insensitive manner. 
 column_name data_type, ...

 data_type : primitive_type
 | array_type
 | map_type
 | record_type
 | union_type
 [ not null ]

 primitive_type: boolean
 | int
 | long
 | float
 | double
 | bytes
 | string

 array_type: array<data_type>

 map_type: map<data_type, data_type>

 record_type: record<field_name:data_type, ...>

 union_type: union<data_type, data_type, ...>

Parameters:
schemaString - the schema to parse
Returns:
the parsed schema object
Throws:
IOException - if there was an exception parsing the schema

enumWith

public static Schema enumWith(String... values)
Creates a Schema of ENUM type, with the given enum values. The set of values given should be unique and must contains at least one value. The ordering of values in the enum type schema would be the same as the order being passed in.

Parameters:
values - Enum values.
Returns:
A Schema of ENUM type.

Parameters:
values - Enum values.
Returns:
A Schema of ENUM type.

recordOf

public static Schema recordOf(String name)
Creates a RECORD Schema of the given name. The schema created doesn't carry any record fields, which makes it only useful to be used as a component schema for other schema type, where the actual schema is resolved from the top level container schema.

Parameters:
name - Name of the record.
Returns:
A Schema of RECORD type.

recordOf

public static Schema recordOf(String name,
                              Schema.Field... fields)
Creates a RECORD Schema with the given name and Fields. The ordering of the fields inside the record would be the same as the one being passed in.

Parameters:
name - Name of the record
fields - All the fields that the record contains.
Returns:
A Schema of RECORD type.
